  <span id="freeText2816216374631932447" style="display:none">Still have a couple hundred pages in the last volume because I got waylaid with other books to review for actual money -- but Foote's <i>Civil War</i> is a true masterpiece. His friend Walker Percy famously called it "an American <i>Iliad</i>," which description I cannot dispute.</span>
