<div id="review_3051249254" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3051249254" />
    <a title="DALE Sabo" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/105507340-dale-sabo"><img alt="DALE Sabo" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/m_50x66-82093808bca726cb3249a493fbd3bd0f.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3051249254?book_show_action=true">Nov 16, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="DALE Sabo" class="user" itemprop="url" name="DALE Sabo" href="/user/show/105507340-dale-sabo">DALE Sabo</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780394749136" href="/book/show/44242.Civil_War">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/105507340-dale-sabo?shelf=history">history</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3051249254" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7619774527708483022">Date read is approximate. The author is a very skilled writer of fiction born in Mississippi in 1916. If you’ve seen Ken Burn’s Civil War documentary you’ve seen him speak at a number of points in the production. <br/><br/>This is not fiction. It’s the result of twenty years if scholarship by a man sympathetic to both sides to some degree. It took me a couple years to finish the three books. It is a sad and beautiful story, true history written with great literary skill. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


