<div id="review_143155371" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/143155371" />
    <a title="Gerry Huntman" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3944964-gerry-huntman"><img alt="Gerry Huntman" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1277896810p2/3944964.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/143155371?book_show_action=true">Jan 23, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Gerry Huntman" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Gerry Huntman" href="/user/show/3944964-gerry-huntman">Gerry Huntman</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer143155371" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9287970989231383496">Forgot about this trio - so I will add a few words...<br/><br/>I am fascinated by the US Civil War and it doesn&apos;t take much to get my interest flowing, if the topic is covered. Then there is Shelby Foote&apos;s masterpiece.<br/><br/>I don&apos;t want to quibble over detail, not that there is much to quibble over, and it can be left to the hard core historians, but Shelby&apos;s work is huge, and easy to read - it is a narrative history, after all. It is immense in size and had to be so, as it covers material - not only the handfu</span>
  <span id="freeText9287970989231383496" style="display:none">Forgot about this trio - so I will add a few words...<br /><br />I am fascinated by the US Civil War and it doesn't take much to get my interest flowing, if the topic is covered. Then there is Shelby Foote's masterpiece.<br /><br />I don't want to quibble over detail, not that there is much to quibble over, and it can be left to the hard core historians, but Shelby's work is huge, and easy to read - it is a narrative history, after all. It is immense in size and had to be so, as it covers material - not only the handful of years when the Civil War actually occurred, but the aftermath and also the historical and cultural significance to Americans, and world citizenry.<br /><br />When I first bought them, I read the entirety in about two weeks. It was that good.<br /><br />Five stars, in part because I love the topic.</span>
  <a data-text-id="9287970989231383496" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
